The paper focuses on social spam detection on Twitter, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of classification algorithms and feature sets, which are common topics in the categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves data mining and information retrieval, which are relevant to the categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
